# ============================================================
# IDENTITY CORE ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: architecture
domain: identity
scope: identity.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of identity in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Identity is the bounded continuity structure
through which a subject remains meaningfully the same subject
across states,
roles,
relations,
and time.

Identity is not merely a display name or identifier token.
It is the authoritative basis
for subject continuity and attributable action.

## architectural_position
Identity sits between:
- subject continuity
- permission/security checks
- role and governance attribution
- history reconstruction
- integration and external reference

## required_behavior
- identity basis must remain explicit
- current and historical identity states must remain distinguishable
- identity continuity must remain attributable
- alias/projection must remain distinguishable from canonical identity

## canonical_rules
- display identity must not overwrite canonical identity
- continuity without basis is prohibited
- historical identity trace must remain queryable
- ambiguous identity fails closed

## state_model
The identity domain distinguishes:
- canonical identity state
- alias/projection identity state
- restricted identity state
- historical identity state
- retired identity state

## actor_boundary
- identity holder
- operator
- reviewer
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if identity basis is unclear, stop identity-sensitive action
- if canonical and projected identity are mixed, fail closed
- if identity becomes historical or retired, preserve trace

## review_checklist
- identity basis is explicit
- continuity model is explicit
- canonical/projection split is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
